{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἑκών</b>, ἑκοῦσα, ἑκόν: <br /> (ϝέκ- [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 9(1).334.12 (_Locrian dialect_), “GDI” 5131b (from Crete), compare γεκαθά\">Refs</a>]; cf. Sanskrit <i>váśmi</i> 'wish'):—<b>readily</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.649, etc.; frequently contrasted with ἄκων, ἑ. ἀέκοντί γε θυμῷ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.43; οὐ γάρ τίς με βίῃ γε ἑ. ἀέκοντα δίηται 7.197; ἑκόνθ᾽ ἑκόντι Ζηνὶ συμπαραστατεῖν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 220; πάρειμι δ᾽ ἄκων οὐχ ἑκοῦσιν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 276; ἑκόντα μήτ᾽ ἄκοντα [prev. author] “Ph.” 771; βίᾳ τε κοὐχ ἑκών [prev. author] “OC” 935 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἑ. παρ᾽ ἑκόντος λαμβάνειν, i.e. by mutual consent, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.44; τὴν φύσιν ἑκοῦσαν καὶ οὐ παθοῦσαν τὰ δέοντα ποιεῖν 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 19.171. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>wittingly, purposely</b>, ἑκὼν δ᾽ ἡμάρτανε φωτός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.372, etc.; σφόδρ᾽ ἑκὼν.. ἀγνοεῖν προσποιούμενος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 29.13. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> in <i>Attic dialect</i> Prose [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare (2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista 241), ἑ. εἶναι\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <b>as far as depends on one's will, as far as concerns one</b>, with a <i>negative</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.104, 8.116, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 37a, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in oblique cases, ὑπὸ σοῦ ἑκόντος εἶναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Grg.” 499c \">Refs</a>]; or in a sentence implying a <i>negative</i>, θαυμάζοιμεν ἂν εἰ.. τις ἑκὼν εἶναι (perhaps delendum).. ἀφικνεῖτα; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 646b: once affirmative, ἑκὼν εἶναι.. οἴχετο 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.164. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> rarely of things, κακὰ ἑ. κοὐκ ἄκοντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1230. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> for <i>adverb</i> see ἑκοντήν, ἑκοντί: regular <i>adverb</i> ἑκόντως is uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aristides Rhetor 2.187, 226J. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1635","accentedUnicode":"ἑκών","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0210","matchingForm":"ἄκων","stepTransliteration":"akōn","gloss":"unwilling","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不甘心","_es_Gloss":"poco dispuesto","_zh_Gloss":"不甘心"},{"strongNumber":"G1595","matchingForm":"ἑκούσιος","stepTransliteration":"hekousios","gloss":"voluntary","_zh_tw_Gloss":"甘心","_es_Gloss":"voluntario ","_zh_Gloss":"甘心"}],"shortDef":"voluntarily, by one’s own choice","mediumDef":"voluntarily, by one’s own choice <br /><b>willing, voluntary, by one’s own choice</b> <ref='Rom.8.20'>Rom. 8:20;</ref> <ref='1Co.9.17'>1Cor. 9:17</ref>*","stepGloss":"voluntarily","stepTransliteration":"hekōn","count":2,"_es_Definition":"por su propia voluntad","_zh_tw_Definition":"自願甘心的 (羅 8:20; 林前 9:17)","_zh_Definition":"自愿甘心的 (罗 8:20; 林前 9:17)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sẵn lòng; tự nguyện","_zh_tw_Gloss":"甘心","_es_Gloss":"voluntariamente ","_zh_Gloss":"甘心"}]}